1
00:01:24,170 --> 00:01:30,250
[Sunshine of My Life]

2
00:01:30,250 --> 00:01:32,880
[Episode 5]

3
00:01:36,540 --> 00:01:39,240
You are stingy.

4
00:01:39,240 --> 00:01:42,590
You're a boss of such a big company yet you're having me pay.

5
00:01:43,320 --> 00:01:45,030
Excuse me. Make way please. Excuse me.

6
00:01:45,030 --> 00:01:46,890
Okay.

7
00:01:46,890 --> 00:01:49,190
There is no place to sit.

8
00:01:50,120 --> 00:01:53,250
Let's sit here. Boss, please help us clean up this table!

9
00:01:53,250 --> 00:01:55,000
Sure!

10
00:01:57,040 --> 00:01:59,580
- May I have the menu?
- Menu.

11
00:01:59,580 --> 00:02:02,330
Sit.

12
00:02:02,330 --> 00:02:06,790
Let me tell you... The bullfrog here is super delicious.

13
00:02:06,790 --> 00:02:09,550
One serving of bullfrog.

14
00:02:09,550 --> 00:02:12,500
You can eat spicy, right?

15
00:02:12,500 --> 00:02:15,580
Lobster. All right! Boss, just these.

16
00:02:15,580 --> 00:02:18,160
Oh, and 2 cans of Sprite.

17
00:02:18,160 --> 00:02:20,920
All right! I'll bring the food to you soon.

18
00:02:20,920 --> 00:02:22,170
Hey, this.

19
00:02:22,170 --> 00:02:23,960
I'm sorry.

20
00:02:25,280 --> 00:02:29,320
Let me tell you... This place's bullfrog is really, really delicious!

21
00:02:29,320 --> 00:02:31,260
After you eat it, I promise you will fall in love with it!

22
00:02:31,260 --> 00:02:32,430
Do you come here often?

23
00:02:32,430 --> 00:02:33,510
This is my canteen.

24
00:02:33,510 --> 00:02:35,010
You are pretty rich.

25
00:02:35,010 --> 00:02:38,160
This-This place is not as expensive as the places you go to.

26
00:02:38,160 --> 00:02:43,060
Besides you are so rich, shouldn't you pay for this meal?

27
00:02:45,160 --> 00:02:46,830
Your Sprite.

28
00:02:52,510 --> 00:02:54,800
Escherichia coli.

29
00:02:59,530 --> 00:03:01,240
What?

30
00:03:01,240 --> 00:03:04,860
Escherichia coli. Give it to me.

31
00:03:04,860 --> 00:03:07,420
The bullfrog is here. Hurry, hurry. Hurry up and eat.

32
00:03:07,420 --> 00:03:10,380
Miss, please bring me a bowl of water.

33
00:03:10,380 --> 00:03:12,840
- Hot water.
- Okay! Coming right up.

34
00:03:12,840 --> 00:03:15,880
Say, it's such a hot summer day yet you're going to drink hot water?

35
00:03:15,880 --> 00:03:18,300
I ordered it for you.

36
00:03:18,300 --> 00:03:19,860
I have a Sprite.

37
00:03:19,860 --> 00:03:21,740
Shouldn't you be drinking hot water right now?

38
00:03:21,740 --> 00:03:23,860
I'm not health conscious.

39
00:03:23,860 --> 00:03:26,310
T-Then you go ahead and drink it.

40
00:03:32,400 --> 00:03:34,230
Chopsticks.

41
00:03:36,950 --> 00:03:39,830
Eating at these places is like this. There's really no problem with it.

42
00:03:39,830 --> 00:03:42,940
My mother is an especially disciplined person.

43
00:03:42,940 --> 00:03:47,580
Then it must be very exhausting to learn all those rules, right?

44
00:03:47,580 --> 00:03:50,970
If you were like this since you were young,

45
00:03:50,970 --> 00:03:53,140
would you think it is exhausting?

46
00:03:56,110 --> 00:03:58,930
B-But I'm different from you. I'm very carefree.

47
00:03:58,930 --> 00:04:02,970
Since I was young, my mom has been very easygoing with me, except for when she's working.

48
00:04:02,970 --> 00:04:07,280
Here, here! E-Eat some bullfrog. It is really tasty.

49
00:04:07,280 --> 00:04:09,100
So you were like a wild child?

50
00:04:09,100 --> 00:04:12,430
What wild child? I'm what's called carefree.

51
00:04:12,430 --> 00:04:14,380
So you were set free to being your individual self?

52
00:04:19,420 --> 00:04:21,220
Who is it?

53
00:04:27,730 --> 00:04:31,210
Lu Zhu? How did you find my home?

54
00:04:31,210 --> 00:04:33,450
The owner of the bar told me.

55
00:04:33,450 --> 00:04:35,160
You didn't go sing last night.

56
00:04:35,160 --> 00:04:37,630
I am worried about you.

57
00:04:43,270 --> 00:04:47,130
Wow! Do you know how to make clothes, too?

58
00:04:47,130 --> 00:04:49,240
These are all my sister's.

59
00:04:49,240 --> 00:04:51,210
Oh...

60
00:04:52,260 --> 00:04:56,960
Don't touch. If you mess it up, my sister will scold me.

61
00:04:58,160 --> 00:04:59,340
Are these done by her, too?

62
00:04:59,340 --> 00:05:01,860
Yes, she is amazing.

63
00:05:03,090 --> 00:05:04,980
A talented woman.

64
00:05:07,010 --> 00:05:10,720
Hey, your home has a lot of fox dolls.

65
00:05:12,720 --> 00:05:16,430
Wow, this Little Prince is so cute!

66
00:05:16,430 --> 00:05:18,330
Can you give it to me?

67
00:05:18,330 --> 00:05:22,600
That... is my sister's. You should put it back.

68
00:05:24,250 --> 00:05:28,800
You don't even know how long I've searched and how far I've walked to find your home.

69
00:05:28,800 --> 00:05:32,820
I care for you so much, yet don't you know to treat me better?

70
00:05:33,720 --> 00:05:35,700
All right! I'll give it to you!

71
00:05:35,700 --> 00:05:36,940
- Really?
- My sister has a lot of these anyway.

72
00:05:36,940 --> 00:05:39,110
Thank you.

73
00:05:42,450 --> 00:05:45,640
My house is in front. You don't need to walk me there. I can get there myself.

74
00:05:45,640 --> 00:05:47,270
I wasn't planning on walking you there.

75
00:05:47,270 --> 00:05:49,500
It just so happens that I have to go this way to get my car.

76
00:05:49,500 --> 00:05:50,780
Get your car?

77
00:05:50,780 --> 00:05:55,910
But... isn't your car parked across from the restaurant we just ate at?

78
00:06:00,400 --> 00:06:05,670
It is so late. Taking a girl back home is also one of my family's rules.

79
00:06:07,220 --> 00:06:08,980
Your family has so many rules.

80
00:06:08,980 --> 00:06:10,720
What?

81
00:06:13,670 --> 00:06:15,680
Say it out loud.

82
00:06:15,680 --> 00:06:18,550
I-I-I nothing.

83
00:06:25,670 --> 00:06:28,250
I discovered that you can eat quite a lot.

84
00:06:29,270 --> 00:06:31,310
I'm all right.

85
00:06:34,330 --> 00:06:39,240
You can stop here. Thank you for bringing me home. Hurry up and head back.

86
00:06:40,660 --> 00:06:42,230
Okay.

87
00:06:48,310 --> 00:06:51,920
Her look of admiration is so direct, isn't it?

88
00:06:57,930 --> 00:07:00,520
Why do you keep looking at me?

89
00:07:02,420 --> 00:07:06,660
Actually, I've been wanting to tell you...

90
00:07:06,660 --> 00:07:08,700
You can be direct.

91
00:07:10,990 --> 00:07:13,410
You have sauce on the corner of your mouth.

92
00:07:17,110 --> 00:07:19,710
You haven't rubbed it off yet.

93
00:07:19,710 --> 00:07:21,530
Let me help you.

94
00:07:32,270 --> 00:07:33,390
Cousin?

95
00:07:33,390 --> 00:07:35,340
Sister?

96
00:07:40,150 --> 00:07:42,080
She's your younger cousin?

97
00:07:43,940 --> 00:07:46,170
This is my younger brother.

98
00:07:49,960 --> 00:07:52,720
- It is so late. Why aren't you—
- Don't misunderstand.

99
00:07:52,720 --> 00:07:54,990
This is my colleague at Cayman.

100
00:07:54,990 --> 00:07:57,700
We are both trainees.

101
00:07:57,700 --> 00:08:02,500
Today, I came... to ask him about tomorrow's class schedule.

102
00:08:02,500 --> 00:08:04,230
- What?
- Right?

103
00:08:04,230 --> 00:08:05,740
Oh, right. Yes.

104
00:08:10,430 --> 00:08:14,380
But why were you two standing so close to each other?

105
00:08:15,690 --> 00:08:17,480
Hurry home.

106
00:08:24,190 --> 00:08:26,420
- What's going on?
- What's going on with you?

107
00:08:26,420 --> 00:08:29,380
W-When I am not home, you bring girls home?

108
00:08:29,380 --> 00:08:32,740
Then, how about you? I haven't even asked why there is a guy bringing you home in the middle of the night.

109
00:08:32,740 --> 00:08:35,080
I asked you first! You haven't answered me yet.

110
00:08:35,080 --> 00:08:37,930
No, you're a girl. I have to be concerned about your safety.

111
00:08:37,930 --> 00:08:40,670
I-I am your older sister!

112
00:08:51,050 --> 00:08:54,400
- Brother...
- Let me ask you, what time is it right now?

113
00:08:54,400 --> 00:08:55,550
It's just past 8:00 p.m.

114
00:08:55,550 --> 00:08:58,070
- It's just past 8:00 p.m?
- Yes.

115
00:08:59,160 --> 00:09:04,660
It's so late after your classes already. Is it appropriate for a lady like you to go to a man's home?

116
00:09:05,230 --> 00:09:08,660
- Brother, how do you know Mo Fan's sister?
- Don't change the subject.

117
00:09:08,660 --> 00:09:12,140
We have a work relationship. I am asking you a question.

118
00:09:12,140 --> 00:09:16,880
Are you guys dating? I feel very strongly like you two are a couple.

119
00:09:19,050 --> 00:09:20,300
- Really.
- Do we seem like a couple?

120
00:09:20,300 --> 00:09:23,080
I feel like you guys are really compatible.

121
00:09:32,850 --> 00:09:34,900
This...

122
00:09:36,540 --> 00:09:40,170
Is it a pair with mine? The two of them—

123
00:09:42,680 --> 00:09:45,070
Wait! Where did you get this?

124
00:09:45,070 --> 00:09:47,430
Mo Fan gave it to me.

125
00:09:47,430 --> 00:09:48,650
W-What are you doing, Brother?

126
00:09:48,650 --> 00:09:50,140
Don't be touching other people's stuff.

127
00:09:50,140 --> 00:09:54,800
- C-Can I not even look at it? Besides, Mo Fan gave it to me!
- That belongs to Mo Fei!

128
00:09:54,800 --> 00:09:58,430
Let me tell you! Regarding your problem, once we get home,

129
00:09:58,430 --> 00:10:00,550
I will discipline you.

130
00:10:07,860 --> 00:10:09,350
He's a grown man

131
00:10:09,350 --> 00:10:13,150
yet he even uses a straw to drink a beverage.

132
00:10:14,850 --> 00:10:17,760
Sister, what man are you talking about?

133
00:10:18,550 --> 00:10:20,690
Who else can it be—

134
00:10:23,010 --> 00:10:25,480
Say, why are you such a gossip?

135
00:10:25,480 --> 00:10:26,830
I'm just curious. Hurry and tell me.

136
00:10:26,830 --> 00:10:30,520
Curious? From what I see, you usually don't care yet now you're curious?

137
00:10:30,520 --> 00:10:33,170
Listen! The two of us have no relationship at all.

138
00:10:33,170 --> 00:10:35,240
No relationship at all?

139
00:10:35,240 --> 00:10:38,180
If there is no relationship, why did he take you home?

140
00:10:41,260 --> 00:10:44,400
How many times have I told you already?

141
00:10:44,400 --> 00:10:47,560
We have only a work relationship.

142
00:10:47,560 --> 00:10:51,830
Aside from that, there is nothing at all!

143
00:10:54,010 --> 00:10:57,570
Wait! I haven't asked you yet! What's your relationship with Lu Zhu?

144
00:10:57,570 --> 00:10:59,530
- Us?
- Yes.

145
00:10:59,530 --> 00:11:03,290
It's very simple. We are simply colleagues.

146
00:11:03,290 --> 00:11:05,600
You two are simply colleagues. Why can't we be the same?

147
00:11:05,600 --> 00:11:07,490
Our relationship is very simple, too, all right?

148
00:11:07,490 --> 00:11:11,300
If that's the case, why are you blushing?

149
00:11:11,300 --> 00:11:15,050
I'm blushing? I just put too much blush on.

150
00:11:15,050 --> 00:11:16,850
What do you know?

151
00:11:20,900 --> 00:11:22,980
You like clapping so much, you brat!

152
00:11:22,980 --> 00:11:24,850
Sister, don't touch me! I depend on my face to make money nowadays.

153
00:11:24,850 --> 00:11:26,870
Depend on your face to make money? Leave!

154
00:11:26,870 --> 00:11:28,990
- Don't annoy me.
- Fine, I'll go.

155
00:11:37,250 --> 00:11:39,500
Did I really blush?

156
00:11:40,970 --> 00:11:43,790
It is just too much blush.

157
00:12:05,580 --> 00:12:07,560
[You seem to be in a very good mood today.]

158
00:12:07,560 --> 00:12:11,880
♫ Like a falling leave falling in front of you ♫

159
00:12:11,880 --> 00:12:13,770
Yes, I am in a very good mood.

160
00:12:13,770 --> 00:12:17,150
Something I have worried about for a long time was finally solved.

161
00:12:19,080 --> 00:12:21,630
[What else?]

162
00:12:22,510 --> 00:12:24,390
Hey, say...

163
00:12:24,390 --> 00:12:28,420
Based on your personality, I can't believe you didn't ask me what I was worried about.

164
00:12:28,420 --> 00:12:30,700
[Probably about the Suzhou embroidery workshop, right?]

165
00:12:31,170 --> 00:12:33,600
You're smart.

166
00:12:33,600 --> 00:12:36,120
The embroidery workshop situation was resolved.

167
00:12:36,120 --> 00:12:39,390
[Aside from Su embroidery, there is nothing else on your mind.]

168
00:12:39,390 --> 00:12:41,060
That's not true!

169
00:12:41,060 --> 00:12:42,540
[Then let's hear it?]

170
00:12:43,070 --> 00:12:48,250
♫  I've dreamt of a more beautiful life but I must stay strong  ♫

171
00:12:48,250 --> 00:12:51,400
It is a secret.

172
00:12:51,400 --> 00:12:54,230
♫ Let the autumn season pass ♫

173
00:12:54,230 --> 00:12:56,920
[I am also really happy today. Do you want to hear about my secret?]

174
00:12:56,920 --> 00:13:01,240
♫  Confess that you are in my prayers ♫

175
00:13:01,240 --> 00:13:03,610
Sure. I have known you for so long,

176
00:13:03,610 --> 00:13:07,010
yet this is the first time I'm hearing you talk about yourself.

177
